An Osogbo Chief Magistrates’ Court in Osun State yesterday sentenced a 19-year-old boy, Olasunkanmi Yekini, to six years in prison for stealing three female underwear and one Tecno mobile phone valued at N6,000.
The magistrate, Rofiat Olayemi, sentenced the convict without any option of fine. The prosecutor, Inspector Jafani Musilimi, had told the court that the convict committed the offense on January 28, about 10a.m., at No. 12, Ibokun Road, Oja-Oba area, Osogbo.
Musilimi, according to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN), said the convict broke into the apartment of a lady, Folashade Ganiyu, and stole three underpants belonging to her inside her bathroom.
He said: “The convict also stole a Techno mobile phone valued at about N6,000 belonging to the complainant.” Musilimi said the convict conducted himself in a manner likely to cause a breach of public peace.
The prosecutor said the offence contravened the provisions of Sections 412 and 249(d) of the Criminal Code, Cap 34, Vol. 11, Laws of Osun, 2002.
The convict was charged with theft and breach of public peace.